# Trivy Ignore File
#
# This file allows you to suppress specific CVE findings from failing the pipeline.
# Use this ONLY for documented exceptions with expiry dates.
#
# Format:
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # Reason for exception | Expires: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Example:
#   CVE-2023-12345  # No fix available; mitigated by network policy | Expires: 2026-04-01
#
# Guidelines:
# - Every exception MUST have a documented reason and expiry date
# - Review all exceptions monthly during security rotation
# - Remove expired exceptions immediately
# - Prefer fixing/upgrading over ignoring
#
# See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/

# --- Exceptions below this line ---
